  <div class="jobs-listing">
  	<span class="bold13">Regional Property Manager - Full Time</span><br />
    <br />
    <div class="jobs-floatr"><a href="/files/EmploymentApplication.pdf">Employment Application</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/files/RegionalJobDescription.pdf">View Job Description</a></div>
    <span class="bold">CORPORATE - California</span> - Los Angeles,California<br />
    <br />
    Apartment Management Consultants, LLC would like to announce the opening of a Regional Property Manager position. <br />
    <br />
		Responsible for performance of operations of sub-region areas with a purpose of creating net operating income reporting lines from the sub-region to the regional office and in turn to the management company. Develop and set project goals to maximize revenue and control expenses. With the assistance of the community staff, prepare annual budgets. Analyze monthly statements and variances for each property and report those variances to the owner. Maximize revenue by control of expenses and/or improved income. <br />
    <br />
		Manages 2-10 Community Managers who supervise a total of 1-10 employees on-site. Responsible for the overall profitability and financial direction, coordination, and evaluation of the communities under his/her supervision. Carries out supervisory responsibilities in accordance with the Company's policies and applicable laws. Responsibilities include interviewing, hiring, and training employees; planning, assigning, and directing work; appraising performance; rewarding and disciplining employees; addressing complaints and resolving problems. <br />
    <br />
		<span class="bold">Contact:</span> Sheena Arb<span class="blue">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span><span class="bold">Phone:</span> (801)676-1646<span class="blue">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span><span class="bold">Fax:</span> (801)676-1646<span class="blue">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span><span class="bold">Email:</span> <a href="mailto:jobs@amcllc.net">Human Resources Manager</a>
  </div>
  <div class="jobs-listing">
  	<span class="bold13">Maintenance Supervisor - Full Time</span><br />
    <br />
    <div class="jobs-floatr"><a href="/files/EmploymentApplication.pdf">Employment Application</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/files/Maintenance SupervisorJobDescription.pdf">View Job Description</a></div>
    <span class="bold">Crystal Creek AZ - Arizona</span> - Phoenix,Arizona<br />
    <br />
    AMC, Utah&#8217;s largest apartment management company has an opening for a Maintenance Supervisor position. The Maintenance Supervisor will be responsible for the oversight of the maintenance team on a daily basis. This is to include schedule and any other employee issues that may arrise. Maintenance Supervisors are also responsible for the daily repair and upkeep of property as well as preparation of vacant units for occupancy. Qualifications: Previous property maintenance or renovation experience required. Pool and HVAC certification a plus. 
